[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92munrealized foreign currency exchange rate gains ( losses )      [0m[92m5222.0  [0m[92m-5459.0 [0m[92m2567.0[0m                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mconsolidated statements of income . since 2007 , we have used foreign currency forward contracts to reduce the risk from [0m     [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92munrealized foreign currency exchange rate gains ( losses )      [0m[92m5222.0  [0m[92m-5459.0 [0m[92m2567.0[0m                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                        [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mmanagement activities . derivatives represent contracts between parties that usually require little or no initial net [0m        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92minvestment and result in one party delivering cash or another type of asset to the other party based on a notional amount [0m    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mand an underlying as specified in the contract . derivative transactions are often measured in terms of notional amount , [0m    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mbut this amount is generally not exchanged and it is not recorded on the balance sheet . the notional amount is the basis to[0m  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mwhich the underlying is applied to determine required payments under the derivative contract . the underlying is a [0m           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mreferenced interest rate ( commonly libor ) , security price , credit spread or other index . residential and commercial [0m     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mreal estate loan commitments associated with loans to be sold also qualify as derivative instruments . the fo...[0m              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mvalue of assets and liabilities , and cash flows . we also enter into derivatives with customers to facilitate their risk [0m    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mmanagement activities . derivatives represent contracts between parties that usually require little or no initial net [0m        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92minvestment and result in one party delivering cash or another type of asset to the other party based on a notional amount [0m    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mand an underlying as specified in the contract . derivative transactions are often measured in terms of notional amount , [0m    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mbut this amount is generally not exchanged and it is not recorded on the balance sheet . the notional amount is the basis to[0m  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mwhich the underlying is applied to determine required payments under the derivative contract . the underlying is a [0m           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mreferenced interest rate ( commonly libor ) , security price , credit spread or other index . residential and commercial [0m     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mreal estate loan commitments associated with loans to be sold also qualify as derivative instruments . the fo...[0m              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
